Wave 9 cirrus9 real-HW capture (/tmp/cirrus9/IMG_2784.jpeg + IMG_2786.jpeg)
showed two correctness regressions from patch 0052's dirty-rect skip-blit:

  1. Sprite trails / ghosts during cutscenes — when a sprite moves from
     position A to position B between frames, the static-prefix skip
     leaves the sprite's old pixels at A in the backbuffer (because we
     skip the bg-tile drawcall whose pixels would have erased them).

  2. Menu items missing — title menu shows only "New game" instead of
     all 5 items. The first-divergence-cliff fires somewhere in the
     menu-text drawcalls, leaving later items un-drawn (or not visibly
     in the dirty rect list).

Both root causes trace to the single-pass algorithm's inability to
identify drawcalls whose output depends on PRIOR drawcalls in the same
frame. A correct implementation needs a 2-pass model (compute all
hashes + dirty regions, THEN execute drawcalls intersecting dirty
region). That's substantial NXEngine refactoring deferred to wave 11+.

This patch flips the default from ON to OFF: existing infrastructure
stays in tree (vector tracking, hash logic, diagnostic instrumentation)
for future debugging, but every drawcall now runs the slow-path /
Approach-B path that worked correctly in waves 6-8. Re-enable for
experimentation via SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=1.

Per-flip perf returns to wave-8 baseline (~6.4 fps title on real Cirrus)
with wave-8's clean visual.
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 22 +++++++++++-----------
 src/graphics/Renderer.h   |  9 ++++++---
 2 files changed, 17 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index 692aec1..b5cdffc 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -597,23 +597,23 @@ bool Renderer::initVideo()
   // mode change or window-surface invalidation).
   _cached_window_surface = SDL_GetWindowSurface(_window);
 
-  // DOS-PORT (patch 0052, Phase 9 wave 9 Lever A): env-var override
-  // for the dirty-rect optimization. Default ON; setting
-  // SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=0 in CONFIG.SYS / AUTOEXEC.BAT
-  // forces every drawcall through the slow path, useful when chasing
-  // a suspected fingerprint-collision regression.
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0052 + 0053, Phase 9 wave 9/10): env-var override
+  // for the dirty-rect optimization. Default OFF — wave 9 cirrus9
+  // capture showed sprite-trail / menu-fragment correctness bugs.
+  // Setting SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=1 in CONFIG.SYS / AUTOEXEC.BAT
+  // re-enables the optimization for testing.
   {
     const char *dr = SDL_getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS");
-    if (dr && dr[0] == '0' && dr[1] == 0)
+    if (dr && dr[0] == '1' && dr[1] == 0)
     {
-      _dirty_rect_enabled = false;
-      LOG_INFO("Renderer::initVideo: dirty-rect tracking DISABLED via "
-               "SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=0");
+      _dirty_rect_enabled = true;
+      LOG_INFO("Renderer::initVideo: dirty-rect tracking ENABLED via "
+               "SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=1 (experimental)");
     }
     else
     {
-      LOG_INFO("Renderer::initVideo: dirty-rect tracking ENABLED "
-               "(set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=0 to disable)");
+      LOG_INFO("Renderer::initVideo: dirty-rect tracking DISABLED "
+               "(set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=1 to enable, experimental)");
     }
   }
   // First frame must be a full refresh — we have no last-frame
diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.h b/src/graphics/Renderer.h
index b578e2d..539e151 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.h
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.h
@@ -176,9 +176,12 @@ class Renderer
     // Periodic paranoia refresh — re-seed the dirty-rect tracker every
     // N flips so any accumulated invariant drift gets corrected.
     static constexpr int FORCE_FULL_REFRESH_EVERY = 60;
-    // Master enable. Default ON; flipped to OFF if the
-    // SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS env var is set to "0".
-    bool _dirty_rect_enabled = true;
+    // Master enable. Default OFF (Phase 9 wave 9 cirrus9 capture
+    // surfaced sprite-trail / menu-fragment correctness bugs in the
+    // single-pass first-divergence-cliff algorithm — full 2-pass
+    // refactor needed for correctness, deferred to a future wave).
+    // Flipped to ON only if SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS is "1".
+    bool _dirty_rect_enabled = false;
     // Diagnostic counters (per-100-flip block + lifetime totals).
     int _dr_total_calls_block = 0;
     int _dr_skipped_calls_block = 0;
